Subject: PRC Feedback forms


Mr. Kaminski:


I would like to try to get on your schedule for a few moments this week to

discuss the draft  PRC 360 evaluation forms (provided below for your info) to

ensure that the criteria and skills and behaviors we have used are adequate

for your employee population.  The generic forms that were presented at the

PRC Committee meeting a week ago may best reflect commercial employees, and

to some extent commercial support employees, and may not be entirely

appropriate for employees in some of the specialized technical and technical

areas.  I would appreciate your input on this so that, if possible and time

permitting, we can try to tailor the form to suit needs across the

organization.


One simple solution may be to add a skills/behaviors block requesting

evaluation and feedback on the employees specific job and performance,

another solution would be to add job specific behaviors and descriptors to

the list of those already developed (second attachment below).  I would

welcome your thoughts and a few moments of your time to chat with you about

this.





Many Thanks,

